item.tinkersarchery.crossbow.description: The crossbow holds shots. It is harder to draw, but that makes shooting it much more satisfying.
item.tinkersarchery.longbow.description: The longbow shoots arrows very far. It takes so much effort to draw, but the arrows hit that much more harder.
item.tinkersarchery.shortbow.description: The shortbow is a simple bow. It has a range comparable to a regular bow, but the potential of a much greater one.
item.tinkersarchery.tinkers_arrow.descri: The arrow is the primary form of ammunition for bows.
material.tconstruct.phantom.arrow: Arrows fly in a straight line, slowing down before starting to fall.
material.tconstruct.phantom.weight: Lighter arrows fly farther and stabler arrows fall slower after beginning to fall.
material.tconstruct.skyslime_vine.bow: Cancels out your velocity added to the arrow.
material.tconstruct.string.bow: The bow is 100% more accurate when fully drawn.
material.tinkersarchery.blazing_string.f: Hot Hot Ouch Ouch Ooh Ouch Hot Ouch
Arrows shot from bows have 0.2 per level more stability, making the follow more favorable trajectories.
Deal more damage the faster you are moving
Yes, this is its formal name
material.tinkersarchery.feather.arrow: Arrows fall under the force of gravity like any other object would.
material.tinkersarchery.feather.weight: Lighter arrows fall slower, and stabler arrows slow down slower.
material.tinkersarchery.galaxy_alloy.bow: Each shot from a bow increases the draw speed of the next shot by 0.2 up to a maximum of 6 times per level.
material.tinkersarchery.galaxy_alloy.enc: Killing an enemy causes your next attack with this weapon to deal 50% per level more damage
material.tinkersarchery.leaf.arrow: Arrows twirl around in the air for some time, and then fall.
material.tinkersarchery.leaf.weight: Lighter arrows slow down slower and stabler arrows twirl tighter.
material.tinkersarchery.paper.arrow: Arrows fly a bit, then loop, then fly parallel to the ground, then loop again, the fly downwards.
material.tinkersarchery.paper.weight: Lighter arrows fly farther and stabler arrows loop tighter.
material.tinkersarchery.silky_cloth.arro: Arrows fly upwards a bit then fall to the ground.
material.tinkersarchery.silky_cloth.bow: Arrows are shot slightly upwards to help with aiming.
material.tinkersarchery.silky_cloth.weig: Weight affects how quickly the arrow flies upwards and falls.
material.tinkersarchery.slime.bow: At full Overslime, the bow has 0.5 more Draw Speed and Draw Weight.
material.tinkersarchery.slime_leaf.arrow: Arrows bounce 5 times in the air.
material.tinkersarchery.slime_leaf.flavo: It's definitely the wood of a slime.
material.tinkersarchery.slime_leaf.weigh: Lighter arrows fall slower, and stabler arrows slow down slower.
material.tinkersarchery.steel_wire.flavo: Clay is no match for power of steel wire!
material.tinkersarchery.tantalum.bow: Bows are 40% per level more accurate per level.
material.tinkersarchery.tantalum.encyclo: Deal 25% per level more damage to enemies below half health.
modifier.tinkersarchery.accurate.flavor: What good is a bow that doesn't shoot where you point?
modifier.tinkersarchery.airborne.descrip: Your velocity is no longer added to the arrow when shot from the bow
modifier.tinkersarchery.autoaim.descript: Arrows shoot in the direction of the nearest entity
modifier.tinkersarchery.burst.descriptio: The next time you consecutively draw your bow, it will draw much faster
modifier.tinkersarchery.chaining.descrip: Deal multiplied damage after killing an enemy
modifier.tinkersarchery.clean.descriptio: The more drawn your bow, the more accurate it is
modifier.tinkersarchery.finishing.descri: Deal more damage to enemies with low health
modifier.tinkersarchery.finishing.flavor: Leaves falling from trees / Snow drifting onto the ground / Life leaving your corpse
modifier.tinkersarchery.gravity_trajecto: Arrows act like they should and fall to the ground in a parabolic trajectory
modifier.tinkersarchery.groovy.descripti: The more you shoot, the faster you draw
modifier.tinkersarchery.haste.descriptio: Magic red dust makes bow draw faster!
modifier.tinkersarchery.highlander.descr: Arrows are shot further at higher altitudes
modifier.tinkersarchery.highlander.flavo: Then I took an arrow to the knee
modifier.tinkersarchery.launching.descri: Arrows are launched at a greater speed
modifier.tinkersarchery.looping_trajecto: Arrows loop once in the air before flying straight then loop again
modifier.tinkersarchery.superslime.descr: The more overslime you have on your bow, the faster you'll draw and the further arrows will go
modifier.tinkersarchery.swiftstrike.desc: Moving faster causes you to deal more damage
modifier.tinkersarchery.swiftstrike.flav: Let's have a chat, shall we?
modifier.tinkersarchery.twirling_traject: Arrows twirl around in the air
modifier.tinkersarchery.uplifting.descri: Arrows are shot slightly upwards to help you aim
modifier.tinkersarchery.weighty.descript: Makes arrows stabler, making them follow more favorable trajectories
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.accuracy.descri:
How accurate the shot is.
This is affected by both the bow and arrow.
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.accuracy.multip: The total accuracy of the tool will be multiplied by this.
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.count.multiplie: The total count of arrows will be multiplied by this.
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.draw_speed.desc:
How fast arrows are drawn.
The exiting velocity of arrows is not linear to how much you draw back the bow.
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.draw_speed.mult: The total draw speed of the tool will be multiplied by this.
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.elasticity.desc:
How fast arrows are shot out of this tool.
The arrow's velocity is taken into account when calculating damage.
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.elasticity.mult: The total draw weight of the tool will be multiplied by this.
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.stability.descr: How stable the trajectory arrows take is.
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.stability.multi: The total stability of arrows will be multiplied by this.
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.weight.descript:
How heavy the arrow is.
Lighter arrows go farther than lighter arrows.
tool_stat.tinkersarchery.weight.multipli: The total weight of the tool will be multiplied by this.
